    • onActionLoginButton

      public void onActionLoginButton(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent) throws IOException, SQLException
      When the user clicks the login button, the login and username text boxes are parsed and sent in a query to the database. If the username and password do not match an entry in the database, a null query is returned and the user is not able to logon. Otherwise, the user is logged in. In either case, the login attempt is written to login_audit.txt
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - login button clicked
      Throws:
      IOException - if main menu is not found
      SQLException - if username and password are not founf

    • onActionCancelButton

      public void onActionCancelButton(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
